line-height:150%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>How confident are you that IndyCar will=
 complement
NASCAR?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">This will be the first time where peop=
le will see the potential for pairing IndyCar and NASCAR together. Part of =
the strategy here was to lift all boats and commingle the two. We=E2=80=99r=
e hopeful that this is going to help both. It also solidifies our leadershi=
p in motorsports. This year will be the first time that both the Indy 500 a=
nd the Daytona 500 will be on the same network. Those are the
two crown jewels of American motorsports.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What =
does your research say? Are they the same fans?</strong></p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">There=E2=80=99s potential to get more crossover between both series. We=
=E2=80=99re going to have IndyCar and NASCAR races on the same day several =
more times. There was only so much we could do with the schedule within the
timeframe that we got the rights in the summer. In future years, you=E2=80=
=99re going to see even more of it.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0=
px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>What should=
 viewers expect this weekend?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The racing will =
be extremely exciting. The league already has an incredible, exciting, fast=
 product on the track. I=E2=80=99m looking for more passes for the lead in
this one race than Formula One will have all season=E2=80=94that=E2=80=99s =
a true stat, by the way. The production quality we=E2=80=99re investing in =
is going to make the sport as sexy as it=E2=80=99s ever been <em>and</em> a=
s approachable as it=E2=80=99s ever been. Motorsports has an issue=E2=80=94=
the stars are completely covered up with helmets, and these really cool loo=
king cars. If you=E2=80=99re tuning in for the first time, you don=E2=80=99=
t know who=E2=80=99s in what car. So, for the first time ever, we invested =
in technology so that when you tune in, you=E2=80=99ll
be able to see who=E2=80=99s driving what car. Just like we have on NASCAR=
=E2=80=94we=E2=80=99ve got some really cool elements around drones and new =
camera angles and new ways to explain the rules and what=E2=80=99s happenin=
g to the viewers.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p =
style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>You=E2=80=99re an Indiana guy=
=2E How much of your upbringing creat=
ed this rights deal?=C2=A0</strong></p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">My=
 first real job in
sports was at the Indy 500 track. I was a summer intern for GTE Sports Mark=
eting. (GTE was a phone company in Indiana and they had a sports marketing =
division.) I got to spend the first month at Indy when the sport was in its=
 heyday. So, I have this connection. I just want to bring Fox=E2=80=99s ass=
ets to a sport that has had such an impact on my life. It is kind of just p=
aying it forward a little bit. On Fox News this week, all the stations were=
 in IndyCar promotion mode, having drivers on-air. We had
an IndyCar on the street on Sixth Avenue in New York yesterday. Fingers cro=
ssed it makes a difference when we get the ratings on Tuesday.</p></div>
